The project:
- represents a Github/Gitea action for increasing versions on a monno/multi repo project
- is written with NodeJs (ES6 / ESM), using JSDoc for documentation
- it is tested using Vitest

Code needs to be written:
- respecting KISS and DRY principles
- as unitary as possible (simple functions, easy to test, easy to read and understand) as human readable as possible
- respecting Uncle Bob's clean code principles
- using functional programming

Requirements:
- do not remove commented code, unless told so; sometimes, to better understand the code step I am analyzing, I am commenting the rest of the code around it
- implement new requirements using TDD approach; write the test first, then write the code to make the test pass


Pseudocode description:
- Inputs:
  - workspaces: list of workspaces to manage versions for (default .:text)
  - platform: what git platform action is running on (default: github)
  - no_pr: create the version commit and tag without preparing a pull request (default: false)
- Steps:
  - [x] detect and store last tag
  - [x] detect and store last commit message
  - [x] gather information about the workspaces that actually changed
  - [x] if not workspaces changed, exit early
    - for those workspaces
      - [x] increase version based on the commit message
      - [x] if no version got changed, exit early
      - [x] apply all calculated versions
      - [x] compose a tree of workspaces to determine root workspace
      - for all tree nodes, except for root, update changelogs
      - for root node
        - if the only node do as tree nodes
        - if not the only node add links to the changed changelogs
      - compose message that will be used as commit or/and PR message
      - if no_pr
        - commit with above message
        - create tag
      - otherwise
        - create separate branch
        - commit with above message
        - create pull request
  - if pull request merge detected
    - create tag
  - print version details and success message
